# person-ms — your overrides.
#
# Loaded AFTER person.defaults.env, so anything you put here wins over
# the snapshot. Compose then layers `environment:` on top of both, which
# is how SEED_USER_*, BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD, and DB_USERNAME/PASSWORD
# get forwarded from quickstart/.env at runtime.
#
# This file is intentionally near-empty — most things you'd want to
# tweak (host ports, admin password, registry, image versions, LLM key)
# live in quickstart/.env one level up. Use this file for the rare
# per-service knob you want to flip without touching the snapshot.
#
# Examples:
#   AUTH_METHODS=password,google             # enable Google sign-in
#   LOCAL_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=...
#   AUTH_METHOD_PASSWORD_REQUIRE_SYMBOL=true # tighten password policy
